            <translation>Such art of stratagems towards the end of book 1 of Cyropaedia: and for specific chapters on Hannibal's wars, especially
                four most astutes ones: [chapters] 26, 36, 37, and 42. [the] very schoole of Machiauel, &amp;platfo[rm]e of pollicy. Such as Aristotle, chapter 11, book 5 of his 'Politics'. With
            the French notes of Ludovicus Regius. But not one equals Polyaenus. </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian" anchor_text="imbushementes">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>A pittfall.</marginalia_text>
